1
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:12,880
Three, two, one.

2
00:00:27,039 --> 00:00:27,760
Lai La.

3
00:00:28,399 --> 00:00:29,679
I've never left the house

4
00:00:29,679 --> 00:00:31,239
after 10 PM.

5
00:00:33,079 --> 00:00:34,759
This is my first beer.

6
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:37,840
Try it out.

7
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,200
What do you think?

8
00:01:00,439 --> 00:01:01,280
It tastes awful.

9
00:01:02,759 --> 00:01:03,719
Same here.

10
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:04,879
But who cares?

11
00:01:05,520 --> 00:01:07,280
That's another tick on the bucket list.

12
00:01:10,814 --> 00:01:13,850
(Lai La and Cai Na's bucket list)

13
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:18,680
(Grab our first beer as adults.)
Done and done.

14
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:20,879
We've finished a whole page.

15
00:01:22,239 --> 00:01:23,319
Time for some new wishes.

16
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:26,799
Is there anything you'd love to try?

17
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,560
I want to see snow.

18
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:33,159
I've never seen snow before.

19
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:37,359
Too bad it's never going to snow here.

20
00:01:39,480 --> 00:01:40,079
Okay.

21
00:01:40,760 --> 00:01:42,879
I'll start a part-time job
when I go to college.

22
00:01:43,319 --> 00:01:44,159
I'll work hard

23
00:01:44,599 --> 00:01:47,000
and take you to Russia,

24
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:48,920
Hokkaido,

25
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,560
and also Mudanjiang.

26
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:53,079
I'll show you all the snow in the world.

27
00:01:56,519 --> 00:01:57,159
Great.

28
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:00,879
We'll both make a ton of money

29
00:02:01,159 --> 00:02:02,439
and travel across the world.

30
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:17,960
We'll watch the snow together.

31
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:31,960
Cheers.

32
00:02:35,084 --> 00:02:39,350
(We'll watch the snow together.)

33
00:04:01,285 --> 00:04:10,370
=The Embers=

34
00:04:11,881 --> 00:04:14,070
=Episode 4=

35
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:45,860
Let's play poker sometimes.

36
00:04:45,879 --> 00:04:46,959
I'm busy.

37
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:48,839
What do you want?

38
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,279
The person you abducted

39
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,680
was not Liao Siyuan.

40
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:58,160
You sent us the photo
of that electric bike.

41
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,480
Xun only ordered us to give you a hand.

42
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,160
Okay.

43
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:20,600
What's going on here?

44
00:05:21,140 --> 00:05:23,180
(1 Hour Ago)
I want to pay my respects to Lai La.

45
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:24,519
Take my bike.

46
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,220
Light some joss sticks for me.

47
00:05:50,639 --> 00:05:51,720
Call Liao Siyuan.

48
00:05:54,044 --> 00:05:55,720
(Qi's Pharmacy)

49
00:05:58,565 --> 00:06:00,970
(Incoming call: Ma Luo)

50
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:03,360
Hello? Ma Luo?

51
00:06:03,900 --> 00:06:05,120
Did you pay your respects?

52
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,360
Save some joss sticks for yourself.

53
00:06:08,079 --> 00:06:09,759
Unless you want your friend dead,

54
00:06:10,199 --> 00:06:13,639
meet me on the roof
of Jialan Tower in ten minutes.

55
00:06:14,439 --> 00:06:15,600
I'm warning you.

56
00:06:16,079 --> 00:06:17,120
No tricks.

57
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,879
If you call the police,

58
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:22,120
I'll cut your friend up

59
00:06:22,519 --> 00:06:23,720
into thin slices

60
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:25,680
like a piece of pork!

61
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,480
Yongli Tower and Jinhu Tower
across the street

62
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:36,720
can see Jialan Tower's roof.

63
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,160
Snipers, find a vantage point.

64
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:38,879
Move in.

65
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:39,830
Once you locate Song En,

66
00:06:39,839 --> 00:06:41,000
I'll lead a team inside.

67
00:06:41,420 --> 00:06:42,510
Is the fire brigade ready?

68
00:06:42,959 --> 00:06:43,720
They are on the way.

69
00:07:06,038 --> 00:07:08,370
(Jialan Tower)

70
00:07:19,199 --> 00:07:19,759
Reporting in.

71
00:07:20,079 --> 00:07:21,079
Song En hasn't shown up.

72
00:07:23,439 --> 00:07:24,680
Liao Siyuan reached the rooftop.

73
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,839
Say hi to your dear friend.

74
00:07:57,319 --> 00:07:57,879
Come on.

75
00:07:59,120 --> 00:07:59,879
Song En,

76
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,120
curse you!

77
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:02,510
Track the signal.

78
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:03,360
Yes.

79
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:04,680
You played dirty!

80
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:06,240
You're a loser!

81
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,000
I'm at the place.

82
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,000
Where are you now?

83
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,720
I think I'm at...

84
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,920
Why should I tell you our location?

85
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,240
I'm the one you want.

86
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:24,680
Just tell me what you want.

87
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:25,959
I told you a long time ago.

88
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:30,120
The smart ones don't live long.

89
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,040
What do you want?

90
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:33,320
Relax.

91
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,840
Let me show you something fun.

92
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,879
Isn't that fun?

93
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,480
Exhilarating, isn't it?

94
00:08:58,919 --> 00:09:00,559
What a surprise, am I right?

95
00:09:03,559 --> 00:09:05,080
I told you not to call the police,

96
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,279
but you did anyway.

97
00:09:08,799 --> 00:09:11,279
It seems like you don't
really care about your buddy.

98
00:09:12,759 --> 00:09:13,639
Now, look at him.

99
00:09:16,799 --> 00:09:17,720
We've been made.

100
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,799
I only wanted a chat.

101
00:09:26,630 --> 00:09:28,860
But you just had to
make things ugly for all of us.

102
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:30,360
Well then,

103
00:09:31,030 --> 00:09:32,060
you may go to hell now.

104
00:09:33,039 --> 00:09:34,159
I'll do as you say.

105
00:09:34,399 --> 00:09:35,240
Let Ma Luo go.

106
00:09:35,519 --> 00:09:36,600
What do you want from me?

107
00:09:37,039 --> 00:09:39,360
Jump down from where you stand.

108
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:50,159
Chief, the fire brigade is here.

109
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:52,080
It's going to take two minutes

110
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:53,279
to inflate the air mattress.

111
00:09:55,279 --> 00:09:56,159
Two minutes...

112
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:10,000
Look! He's going to jump!

113
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:27,000
I'm dying anyway.

114
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,320
Just tell me.

115
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,960
Why did you kill Cai Na and Lai La?

116
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:34,279
Worry about yourself.

117
00:10:35,399 --> 00:10:37,399
It wasn't easy to make it this far.

118
00:10:37,519 --> 00:10:39,200
I'm never letting you ruin it for me.

119
00:10:40,399 --> 00:10:41,159
I know it.

120
00:10:42,159 --> 00:10:45,080
I know you've done nasty things
to set me up.

121
00:10:45,799 --> 00:10:47,919
How dare you stand there

122
00:10:47,919 --> 00:10:48,840
and loathe me

123
00:10:49,039 --> 00:10:50,320
while playing the victim?

124
00:10:53,879 --> 00:10:56,519
You'll suffer the same fate
as Liao Zhibai.

125
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:59,039
As great as he was, it was pointless.

126
00:10:59,519 --> 00:11:01,159
He messed with the wrong man.

127
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:04,200
He deserved to die in that fire.

128
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:09,679
There was a fire at my house
ten years ago.

129
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,159
Was it your doing?

130
00:11:13,759 --> 00:11:15,399
You have 30 seconds
to jump off the roof

131
00:11:15,399 --> 00:11:16,799
unless you want your buddy

132
00:11:17,519 --> 00:11:18,879
to be sliced in halves

133
00:11:18,879 --> 00:11:19,960
like a piece of meat!

134
00:11:23,399 --> 00:11:24,440
Can you guarantee

135
00:11:26,279 --> 00:11:27,120
Ma Luo will be safe

136
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,200
if I do as you say?

137
00:11:29,279 --> 00:11:30,679
Why should I guarantee anything?

138
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:32,559
Ten!

139
00:11:49,639 --> 00:11:50,320
Wait.

140
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,480
Don't take me for a fool.

141
00:11:54,559 --> 00:11:56,159
The rescue team brought an air mattress.

142
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:58,639
I want you to move to the north side

143
00:11:58,639 --> 00:12:00,000
of the roof!

144
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:01,279
Five!

145
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:03,559
Four!

146
00:12:04,039 --> 00:12:04,679
Target located.

147
00:12:04,679 --> 00:12:05,399
Team One, move in!

148
00:12:08,679 --> 00:12:09,279
Three!

149
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:15,799
Two!

150
00:12:21,399 --> 00:12:22,000
One!

151
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:37,480
A young man

152
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:38,480
fell off Jialan Tower

153
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:39,500
and died from the drop.

154
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:42,840
It's been told that the deceased
studied early childhood education.

155
00:12:48,759 --> 00:12:49,440
Where is Song En?

156
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:51,080
Where is Song En?

157
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:57,720
This is my fault!

158
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,919
Liao Siyuan died because of me.

159
00:13:00,639 --> 00:13:01,279
It was...

160
00:13:03,159 --> 00:13:04,159
It was all because of me!

161
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:23,080
Hello, officer.

162
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:28,039
The deceased is my friend.

163
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,440
May I know

164
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:31,519
when I can

165
00:13:32,159 --> 00:13:34,080
see him again?

166
00:13:34,679 --> 00:13:35,480
Who do you mean?

167
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,440
The man who jumped off the building,

168
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:39,399
Liao Siyuan.

169
00:13:40,159 --> 00:13:41,559
Liao Siyuan?

170
00:13:41,759 --> 00:13:42,639
Oh, I remember now.

171
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:44,960
Processing the body

172
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:46,279
isn't a simple task.

173
00:13:46,759 --> 00:13:47,720
Wait for our call.

174
00:13:48,159 --> 00:13:50,080
We'll contact you
if we have any updates.

175
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:32,080
Hello?

176
00:14:32,639 --> 00:14:33,720
Liao Siyuan is dead.

177
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:36,519
The one you anticipated never showed up.

178
00:14:36,799 --> 00:14:38,039
I'm leaving Buhe.

179
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:39,840
You did a great job.

180
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:41,000
He is very pleased.

181
00:14:41,639 --> 00:14:42,759
Go into hiding.

182
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:44,960
Leave the rest to us.

183
00:14:45,559 --> 00:14:46,159
Rest easy.

184
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:48,559
Very well.

185
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:56,360
Sir,

186
00:14:57,519 --> 00:14:59,440
perhaps we overcomplicated things.

187
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:01,679
If he was alive,

188
00:15:03,159 --> 00:15:04,240
he'd make a move.

189
00:15:06,799 --> 00:15:08,919
How much does Song En
know at this point?

190
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:11,240
Basically nothing.

191
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:13,159
However, he was a small part

192
00:15:13,159 --> 00:15:14,519
of the fire from years ago.

193
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:13,879
Who is it?

194
00:16:16,759 --> 00:16:17,559
Who are you?

195
00:16:18,559 --> 00:16:19,159
Who are you?

196
00:16:19,790 --> 00:16:21,960
My identity is not your concern.

197
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:23,840
More importantly,

198
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:27,639
I planted something inside your belly.

199
00:16:28,559 --> 00:16:30,879
It's the same thing
you did to those girls.

200
00:16:36,399 --> 00:16:38,279
What did you

201
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:40,200
put inside me?

202
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:41,759
What is it?

203
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:46,240
Some adorable little creatures.

204
00:16:48,919 --> 00:16:49,720
Stay still.

205
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,639
They might crawl out of you.

206
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:03,960
Who are you?

207
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:05,799
Who are you?

208
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:17,759
Are you that eager to find out?

209
00:17:21,839 --> 00:17:23,240
So be it.

210
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:35,319
Officer.

211
00:17:35,359 --> 00:17:36,599
Are you arresting Song En?

212
00:17:36,599 --> 00:17:37,359
Take me with you.

213
00:17:37,359 --> 00:17:38,480
It's a city-wide manhunt.

214
00:17:38,480 --> 00:17:39,119
Go home.

215
00:17:39,119 --> 00:17:40,319
We'll keep you posted.

216
00:17:40,319 --> 00:17:40,880
Wait...

217
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:55,000
Go on, I'll take you there.

218
00:18:13,559 --> 00:18:14,279
A ghost!

219
00:18:20,599 --> 00:18:21,440
No way!

220
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:22,620
The police station is haunted!

221
00:18:24,759 --> 00:18:25,960
Coming or not?

222
00:18:30,559 --> 00:18:31,400
Where to?

223
00:18:32,519 --> 00:18:33,119
Siyuan...

224
00:18:35,119 --> 00:18:36,519
I know I owe you my life.

225
00:18:36,519 --> 00:18:37,519
I'll have to repay you.

226
00:18:38,079 --> 00:18:39,079
But...

227
00:18:39,559 --> 00:18:41,039
Just give me a few days.

228
00:18:41,759 --> 00:18:43,400
Wait until I've avenged you.

229
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:45,440
Catch this.

230
00:18:49,759 --> 00:18:50,640
Isn't this yours?

231
00:18:54,279 --> 00:18:55,279
You're alive?

232
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:57,319
Siyuan! Are you alive?

233
00:19:00,839 --> 00:19:02,680
We run a fake charity organization.

234
00:19:03,279 --> 00:19:05,640
We target girls
from underprivileged families.

235
00:19:06,599 --> 00:19:09,200
We use overseas scholarships as a front

236
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:11,880
to control them.

237
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:14,960
We force them...

238
00:19:18,880 --> 00:19:19,599
into prostitution.

239
00:19:20,279 --> 00:19:21,400
If they are highly educated,

240
00:19:21,540 --> 00:19:23,960
young, and pretty,
they will be forced to sell their eggs.

241
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:26,640
Then, we look for healthy
surrogate mothers.

242
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:30,880
Chief.

243
00:19:32,119 --> 00:19:33,680
We found a thumb drive in the safe.

244
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:35,200
I printed out the files.

245
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:42,960
This is a price list.

246
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:45,319
Yes.

247
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:48,279
It's 2,000 USD per night.

248
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:51,279
Each egg is 5,000 USD.

249
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:54,640
The service of each surrogate mother
is 150 grand.

250
00:19:55,020 --> 00:19:56,750
We even give them the full recording...

251
00:19:56,759 --> 00:19:57,400
Enough.

252
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:07,839
Do you know Lai La?

253
00:20:09,119 --> 00:20:09,799
Yes.

254
00:20:11,359 --> 00:20:13,200
She came to Song En's clinic.

255
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:16,359
Song En thought she looked
young and healthy.

256
00:20:16,839 --> 00:20:18,160
He was going to lure her in,

257
00:20:18,599 --> 00:20:19,599
but she wasn't interested

258
00:20:19,599 --> 00:20:20,880
in studying abroad.

259
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:23,960
She only worked part-time
to save up money.

260
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:26,400
Our usual method didn't work on her.

261
00:20:27,079 --> 00:20:28,759
Our plan failed.

262
00:20:30,119 --> 00:20:30,799
However,

263
00:20:32,759 --> 00:20:34,319
she introduced Cai Na to us.

264
00:20:37,680 --> 00:20:39,920
What about the child Lai La was bearing?

265
00:20:42,839 --> 00:20:44,200
That happened afterward.

266
00:20:45,440 --> 00:20:47,119
One day, Song En asked me

267
00:20:47,839 --> 00:20:49,119
to conduct a surgery.

268
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,960
I only knew it was Lai La
when I got there.

269
00:20:52,039 --> 00:20:53,960
We are terribly sorry about Cai Na.

270
00:20:55,119 --> 00:20:56,680
She had great genes.

271
00:20:58,799 --> 00:20:59,599
What a shame.

272
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:02,480
I don't have a suitable
surrogate mother.

273
00:21:03,839 --> 00:21:05,039
After much pondering,

274
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,559
you are the best candidate.

275
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:14,640
I don't know the specifics.

276
00:21:15,799 --> 00:21:16,720
In other words,

277
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:20,200
Lai La was carrying Cai Na's child.

278
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:24,119
Yes.

279
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:29,599
Why did Song En kill Lai La?

280
00:21:33,160 --> 00:21:34,119
No idea.

281
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:43,799
When we first learned
about Lai La's death,

282
00:21:45,359 --> 00:21:46,559
I could tell

283
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:48,839
Song En was shocked.

284
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:52,319
It wasn't easy finding
a suitable surrogate mother.

285
00:21:52,980 --> 00:21:55,140
He was hoping to use Lai La
to make a fortune.

286
00:21:58,359 --> 00:22:00,119
I doubt he killed Lai La.

287
00:22:01,319 --> 00:22:02,200
Can you prove it?

288
00:22:03,880 --> 00:22:05,599
